OrderSubsystem

Class Order

  • java.lang.Object
    • OrderSubsystem.Order

  • public class Order
extends java.lang.Object
    This Class implements an Order with specific private attributes tied to the Order, as well as mutators and accessor's so the interfaces can work with the object in a flexible way Also added a toString in case for printing purposes.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    James McCarthy

      • Order

        public Order(java.lang.String orderIdIn,
             java.util.LinkedList<ProductManagementSystem.Product> productsIn,
             double salesTotalIn,
             OrderSubsystem.Address addressIn,
             OrderSubsystem.CreditCard cc,
             application.Account account)

        This Constructs an order with a specified Order Id, A List of Products, Sales Total, Address Object, and a Credit Card Object. Also also used the arrayLists size method to get the productQuantity and the orderDate = new Date(); will get the date of the order when it is created.

        Parameters:
        orderIdIn - - The id passed into the Order
        productsIn - - the List of Products for the Order
        salesTotalIn - - the Sales total Of the Order
        addressIn - - The Address for the Order ( we assume billing and shipping address are the same)
        cc - - The Credit Card Object associated with the order.
